● Phase 5 summary 

  Continuing with the Phase 5 QR/LQ bug fix. Let me read both files and apply the corrections.

● Root cause of both bugs:

  1. qr_extract_Q: Uses apply_householder_right (Q = Q * H_j) but needs apply_householder_left (Q = H_j * Q) to build Q = H_0 * H_1 * ... * H_{k-1} from
  right to left.
  2. lq_extract_Q: Uses reverse iteration with left application, producing Q = H_0 * ... * H_{k-1}, but LQ needs Q = H_{k-1} * ... * H_0, which requires
  forward iteration with left application.

  Summary of fixes:
  - qr_extract_Q: Changed apply_householder_right(Q, v, tau(j), 0, j) → apply_householder_left(Q, v, tau(j), j, 0) to correctly build Q = H_0 * H_1 * ... *
  H_{k-1}
  - lq_extract_Q: Changed reverse iteration to forward iteration to correctly build Q = H_{k-1} * ... * H_0

  Phase 5 delivered:
  - 12 operation headers: trace, random, lower/upper trisolve, LU, householder, QR, LQ, cholesky, inv, ILU(0), IC(0)
  - 5 test files with 21 total passing tests (up from 16 in Phase 4)


