  Key design decisions:

  - Forwarding-ref conditional storage: lvalue operands stored by const T&, rvalue operands stored by value T — prevents dangling references when capturing
  expressions with auto
  - Matrix-matrix multiply stays eager: returns concrete dense2D to avoid aliasing bugs (e.g., auto C = A*B; A = C; pattern in SVD/QR) and O(n^3)-per-element
   recomputation
  - C++20 concepts replace CRTP: expression types simply satisfy Matrix/Vector concepts — no inheritance hierarchy needed


